As baby gets bigger and so do their clothes, you can use larger zip lock bags as travel vacumm bags by just rolling the air out of it, making it more compact. I took two of my children on a winter holiday overseas and was able to pack a full set of clothes (jeans, hoodie, t-shirt, thermal pants, thermal shirt, socks, fleece neck warmer, beanie, underwear) on the plane so that before we hit our destination, I was able to change them into warmer clothes on the plane. You can also use them to carry nappies, making them more compact, especially as they get bigger in size. I used the largest zip lock bags from Ikea (6L for clothes, 4.5L for nappies). I have a similar bag to your nappy bag and was able to fit all that plus more into that bag for two children aged 18 months and 4 years👍🏼
